-- China's shares open up over 1 pct as HK-Shanghai stock link debuts
-- By Lu Jianxin and Kazunori Takada
-- Sun Nov 16, 2014 08:29PM EST
-- None



SHANGHAI, Nov 17 (Reuters) - Chinese shares rose at open on Monday as a landmark trading scheme linking the Shanghai and Hong Kong stock exchanges kicked off.

The CSI300 index <.CSI300> of top Chinese shares rose 1.3 percent to 2,613.5 points, while the Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> gained 1.1 percent to 2,506.7 points.